Organizations & Special Programs





      View Menu
      
Down arrow icon















            Special Programs
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Chicago Symposium Series
                    

                Inter-disciplinary forum bringing together educators interested in improving the teaching of math and science
            









                            Undergraduate Mathematics Symposium (UMS)
                    

                Undergraduate mathematical research conference held at UIC every Fall
            









                            MSCS Undergraduate Research Laboratory (MURL)
                    

                An organization coordinating undergraduate research projects in MSCS
            









                            CryptoClub
                    

                CryptoClub.org is a website where mainly primary school students can learn and apply cryptography.
            









                            RTG
                    

                Research Training Group supported by NSF
            









            Student Organizations
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Undergraduate Math Club
                    

                Club for undergraduates interested in mathematics.
            









                            Symbols of Inclusion
                    

                The mission of Symbols of Inclusion is twofold. First, we aim to provide a supportive community at UIC for women, historically underrepresented students, and gender and sexual minority students of mathematics.
            









                            Mathematics Graduate Student Association (MGSA)
                    

                Student organization for graduate students in our department.
            









                            Association for Women in Mathematics (AWM)
                    

                UIC student chapter of the AWM
            









                            Society of Industrial and Applied Mathematics
                    

                UIC student chapter of SIAM, the Society of Industrial and Applied Mathematics
            









            Support Organizations
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            SACNAS
                    

                Society for the Advancement of Chicanos and Native Americans in Science; fosters success in STEM fields
            









                            Women in Science and Engineering (WISE)
                    

                WISE program supports the success of women in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics
            









                            WISEST
                    

                Women in Science and Engineering System Transformation, a faculty program at UIC
            












